<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<appendix xml:id="app-tables" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title><m>z</m>-score tables</title>
  <section xml:id="sec-z-tables-neg">
    <title><m>z</m>-score table: negative <m>z</m>-scores</title>
    <idx><h>z-score tables</h><h>negative z</h></idx>
    <p>
      The table below gives the area to the <em>left</em> of the given (negative) <m>z</m>-score
      under the standard normal distribution.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="sec-z-tables-pos">
    <title><m>z</m>-score table: positive <m>z</m>-scores</title>
    <idx><h>z-score tables</h><h>positive z</h></idx>
    <p>
      The table below gives the area to the <em>left</em> of the given (positive) <m>z</m>-score
      under the standard normal distribution.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="sec-z-tables-online">
    <title>Online <m>z</m>-score calculators</title>
    <idx><h>z-score tables</h><h>online</h></idx>
    <p>
      Many online calculators can find areas under the standard normal distribution.
      For instance, the GeoGebra normal distribution calculator at
      <url href="https://www.geogebra.org/m/nSqSnSnK">geogebra.org</url>.
    </p>
  </section>
</appendix>
